Phase 1 Tasks 4-5 of kb_benchmark analyzer-v2.

verilogExtractor (src/extraction/languages/verilog.ts) using node-type
names Phase 0 measured against tree-sitter-verilog v1.0.3:

  classTypes:         module/package/class declaration
  interfaceTypes:     interface_declaration
  methodTypes:        function/task declaration (inside class container)
  functionTypes:      function/task declaration (top-level)
  importTypes:        include_directive, package_import_declaration
  callTypes:          subroutine_call
  instantiationTypes: module/checker/udp instantiation (new field — see below)
  variableTypes:      parameter/net/data declaration
  resolveName:        BFS for first simple_identifier descendant; tree-sitter-
                      verilog rarely uses named fields, so most declared names
                      come from "first identifier under the header" rather than
                      a named-field child.

The framework extension: a new optional `instantiationTypes` field on
LanguageExtractor lets per-language extractors route language-specific
binding/instantiation syntax through the existing extractInstantiation
path (which emits `instantiates` references targeting the type's first
named child). The dispatcher checks both INSTANTIATION_KINDS (built-in)
and `extractor.instantiationTypes` in both visit walkers.

Why this is needed for Verilog: tree-sitter-verilog cannot statically
disambiguate `child u(.clk(clk))` between module/UDP/checker
instantiation forms. All three are listed in instantiationTypes; the
target identifier is whatever the grammar tagged as the type name.
Emitting `instantiates` (not `calls`) is semantically more accurate —
a module instance isn't a function call.

Registry edits:
- src/extraction/languages/index.ts: import + register verilogExtractor.
- src/extraction/grammars.ts: add verilog to the local-vendored-grammar
  loader list so the WASM resolves from src/extraction/wasm/ instead of
  tree-sitter-wasms/out/ (which doesn't ship verilog).

Tests (__tests__/verilog-extractor.test.ts, with 3 fixtures):
- Entity extraction: module/package/interface/class/function/task all
  surface with correct names (functions inside modules → 'method' kind,
  top-level functions → 'function' kind).
- Instantiations: 3 different instance syntaxes all produce
  `instantiates` unresolvedReferences naming target 'child'.
- Conditional/case/always blocks: extract the parent module without
  aborting.

378/378 existing tests in __tests__/extraction.test.ts still pass under
node@22. (Under system node@20 they all fail at SQLite init for an
unrelated reason — node:sqlite needs ≥22.5.)
